{
  "info": {
    "name": "SpringBoot Flow API",
    "description": "Execution flow demonstration for Spring Boot. Each folder/request maps to a distinct flow through the layer stack: Filter → Interceptor → AOP → Controller → Service → Exception Handler.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "flow-demo-api-collection",
    "version": {
      "major": 2,
      "minor": 0,
      "patch": 0
    }
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Execution Flows",
      "description": "7 endpoints — each demonstrates a distinct execution path through the layer stack.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Flow 1 — Minimal (Controller Only)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/hello",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "hello"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 1 — Minimal path. No validation. No service call.\n\nStack: Filter → Interceptor → AOP → Controller → AOP → Interceptor → Filter"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has message and timestamp\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.message).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.timestamp).to.exist;",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 2 — Full (Bean Validation + Service)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"John Doe\",\n  \"email\": \"john.doe@example.com\",\n  \"department\": \"Engineering\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 2 — Full path through all layers.\n\nStack: Filter → Interceptor → AOP → Controller → @Valid → Service → AOP → Interceptor → Filter"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has user data with id\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.id).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.name).to.eql(\"John Doe\");",
                  "    pm.expect(json.email).to.eql(\"john.doe@example.com\");",
                  "    pm.expect(json.department).to.eql(\"Engineering\");",
                  "    pm.expect(json.createdAt).to.exist;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"user_id\", pm.response.json().id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 3 — Programmatic Guard (valid id — happy path)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/5",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "5"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 3 — Valid ID. Manual guard (id > 0) passes in controller. Proceeds to service.\n\nStack: Filter → Interceptor → AOP → Controller (id > 0 ✓) → Service → AOP → Interceptor → Filter\n\nFor exception branch (id <= 0), see 'Exception Paths' folder."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response contains user\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.id).to.eql(5);",
                  "    pm.expect(json.name).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.email).to.exist;",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 4 — Unhandled Exception (RuntimeException → GlobalExceptionHandler)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/error-demo",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "error-demo"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 4 — Controller throws RuntimeException. Caught by @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class) in GlobalExceptionHandler.\n\nStack: Filter → Interceptor → AOP → Controller → RuntimeException → AOP @AfterThrowing → GlobalExceptionHandler → Interceptor afterCompletion → Filter"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 500\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(500));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"GlobalExceptionHandler error response\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql(500);",
                  "    pm.expect(json.error).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.message).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.timestamp).to.exist;",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 5 — Startup + Bean Lifecycle Info",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/startup-info",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "startup-info"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 5 — Returns startup and bean lifecycle events captured during boot.\n\nStack: Filter → Interceptor → AOP → Controller → StartupInfoStore.toResponse() → AOP → Interceptor → Filter\n\nThe 'startupSequence' array in the response shows every lifecycle hook that fired in order:\n  [1] EnvironmentPostProcessor  — BEFORE context, injects app.startup.timestamp\n  [2] BeanFactoryPostProcessor  — inspects BeanDefinitions before instantiation\n  [3] BeanPostProcessor.before  — wraps each bean before @PostConstruct\n  [4] @PostConstruct             — StartupInfoStore + BeanLifecycleDemoBean init\n  [5] BeanPostProcessor.after   — AOP proxies (JDK / CGLIB) created here\n  [7] ApplicationRunner.run()   — StartupApplicationRunner, context fully refreshed\n  [8] CommandLineRunner.run()   — ExecutionFlowDemoRunner, same phase\n\nKey classes: StartupInfoStore, StartupApplicationRunner, StartupEnvironmentPostProcessor,\n             FlowBeanFactoryPostProcessor, FlowBeanPostProcessor, BeanLifecycleDemoBean"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has startup metadata\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.applicationName).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.startupTimestamp).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.totalBeanCount).to.be.a('number').and.greaterThan(0);",
                  "    pm.expect(json.flowBeanCount).to.be.a('number').and.greaterThan(0);",
                  "    pm.expect(json.flowBeanNames).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"startupSequence captures lifecycle hooks\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.startupSequence).to.be.an('array').and.have.length.greaterThan(0);",
                  "    const seq = json.startupSequence.join(' ');",
                  "    pm.expect(seq).to.include('EnvironmentPostProcessor');",
                  "    pm.expect(seq).to.include('BeanFactoryPostProcessor');",
                  "    pm.expect(seq).to.include('ApplicationRunner');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 6 — Async Demo (fire-and-forget @Async)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/async-demo",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "async-demo"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 6 — @Async direct demo (fire-and-forget).\n\nWhat to observe in the logs (order matters):\n  1. CONTROLLER - EXECUTING   (HTTP thread)\n  2. CONTROLLER - RETURNING   (HTTP thread — 202 sent BEFORE async finishes)\n  3. ASYNC SERVICE - STARTED  (task-N thread)\n  4. ASYNC SERVICE - FINISHED (task-N thread — ~2s after response)\n\nTip: also try Flow 7 (GET /api/users/event-demo) to observe the event chain:\n  sync listener on HTTP thread → HTTP 200 sent → async listener on task-N.\n\nStack: Filter → Interceptor → AOP → Controller → AsyncDemoService.runAsync() [thread pool] → HTTP 202"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 202 Accepted\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has message and requestId\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.message).to.include('Async task started');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.requestId).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.hint).to.exist;",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 8 — Cache Layer (@Cacheable / @CachePut / @CacheEvict)",
          "description": "FLOW 8 — Caching Layer demo. Run the requests in order to observe every cache annotation in action.\n\nRecommended sequence:\n  8a → GET  /{id}        — MISS  (~500ms, logs 'CACHE - MISS')\n  8b → GET  /{id}        — HIT   (instant, NO 'MISS' log line)\n  8c → PUT  /{id}?data=X — @CachePut  (always runs + updates cache)\n  8b → GET  /{id}        — HIT   with new value\n  8d → DELETE /{id}      — @CacheEvict (removes one entry)\n  8a → GET  /{id}        — MISS  again\n  8e → DELETE /          — @CacheEvict(allEntries=true)\n\nCache name  : 'users'\nCacheManager: ConcurrentMapCacheManager (simple in-memory, no server required)\nSee also    : GET /actuator/caches to inspect cache state",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Flow 8a — @Cacheable MISS (first call, ~500ms)",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/cache-demo/1",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "users", "cache-demo", "1"]
                },
                "description": "FLOW 8a — @Cacheable cache MISS.\n\nid=1 is NOT in the cache yet. CacheDemoService.getUser(1) runs fully:\n  1. Logs 'CACHE - MISS — id=1 NOT in cache'\n  2. Simulates 500ms DB call\n  3. Stores result in cache 'users' under key=1\n  4. Returns data\n\nexpected body.elapsedMs ≈ 500\nexpected body.cacheHint  = 'MISS — loaded from source (~500ms)'\n\nRun Flow 8b immediately after to see the HIT."
              },
              "response": [],
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                      "",
                      "pm.test(\"Cache MISS — elapsedMs > 400\", () => {",
                      "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json.elapsedMs).to.be.above(400);",
                      "    pm.expect(json.cacheHint).to.include('MISS');",
                      "});",
                      "",
                      "pm.test(\"Result contains expected fields\", () => {",
                      "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json.result.id).to.eql(1);",
                      "    pm.expect(json.result.data).to.exist;",
                      "    pm.expect(json.result.source).to.eql('database');",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "name": "Flow 8b — @Cacheable HIT (second call, instant)",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/cache-demo/1",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "users", "cache-demo", "1"]
                },
                "description": "FLOW 8b — @Cacheable cache HIT.\n\nid=1 IS in the cache (populated by Flow 8a). Spring intercepts BEFORE CacheDemoService.getUser(1) is called:\n  - The method body does NOT execute (NO 'CACHE - MISS' log line)\n  - Cached value returned immediately (~0ms)\n\nexpected body.elapsedMs  < 100\nexpected body.cacheHint  = 'HIT — returned from cache instantly'\n\nKey insight: the ABSENCE of the 'MISS' log line is the proof the cache worked."
              },
              "response": [],
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                      "",
                      "pm.test(\"Cache HIT — elapsedMs < 100\", () => {",
                      "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json.elapsedMs).to.be.below(100);",
                      "    pm.expect(json.cacheHint).to.include('HIT');",
                      "});",
                      "",
                      "pm.test(\"Same data as MISS\", () => {",
                      "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json.result.id).to.eql(1);",
                      "    pm.expect(json.result.source).to.eql('database');",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "name": "Flow 8c — @CachePut (always runs + updates cache)",
              "request": {
                "method": "PUT",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/cache-demo/1?data=Alice%20(Updated)",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "users", "cache-demo", "1"],
                  "query": [
                    { "key": "data", "value": "Alice (Updated)" }
                  ]
                },
                "description": "FLOW 8c — @CachePut.\n\nUnlike @Cacheable, @CachePut ALWAYS executes the method body AND updates the cache.\nUse for write operations to keep the cache consistent with the data source.\n\nAfter this call:\n  - 'CACHE - @CachePut' log line appears (method ran)\n  - cache 'users' key=1 now holds the new data\n  - GET /api/users/cache-demo/1 (8b) returns the updated value instantly"
              },
              "response": [],
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                      "",
                      "pm.test(\"@CachePut annotation confirmed\", () => {",
                      "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json.annotation).to.eql('@CachePut');",
                      "    pm.expect(json.result.data).to.include('Updated');",
                      "    pm.expect(json.result.source).to.include('updated');",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "name": "Flow 8d — @CacheEvict (evict one entry)",
              "request": {
                "method": "DELETE",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/cache-demo/1",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "users", "cache-demo", "1"]
                },
                "description": "FLOW 8d — @CacheEvict.\n\nRemoves the entry for id=1 from cache 'users'.\nAfter this call, GET /api/users/cache-demo/1 will be a MISS (~500ms) again."
              },
              "response": [],
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                      "",
                      "pm.test(\"@CacheEvict annotation confirmed\", () => {",
                      "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json.annotation).to.eql('@CacheEvict');",
                      "    pm.expect(json.evictedId).to.eql(1);",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "name": "Flow 8e — @CacheEvict allEntries (clear entire cache)",
              "request": {
                "method": "DELETE",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/cache-demo",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "users", "cache-demo"]
                },
                "description": "FLOW 8e — @CacheEvict(allEntries=true).\n\nClears ALL entries from cache 'users' at once.\nEvery subsequent GET for any id will be a MISS until repopulated."
              },
              "response": [],
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                      "",
                      "pm.test(\"allEntries annotation confirmed\", () => {",
                      "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json.annotation).to.include('allEntries');",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "name": "Flow 8f — Verify Evict (should be MISS again)",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/cache-demo/1",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "users", "cache-demo", "1"]
                },
                "description": "FLOW 8f — Verify cache is empty after eviction.\n\nRun after Flow 8d or 8e. id=1 is no longer cached.\nExpect: elapsedMs > 400 (MISS — loads from source again)."
              },
              "response": [],
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                      "",
                      "pm.test(\"MISS after eviction — elapsedMs > 400\", () => {",
                      "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json.elapsedMs).to.be.above(400);",
                      "    pm.expect(json.cacheHint).to.include('MISS');",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 7 — Event Demo (UserProcessedEvent chain)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/event-demo?name=Demo%20User&email=demo%40example.com",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "event-demo"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "name",  "value": "Demo User" },
                { "key": "email", "value": "demo@example.com" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 7 — Dedicated event chain demo.\n\nPublishes UserProcessedEvent directly from the controller. Isolates event observation from the user-creation flow (Flow 2).\n\nWhat to observe in the logs (order matters):\n  1. CONTROLLER - EXECUTING            (HTTP thread — http-nio-exec-N)\n  2. EVENT LISTENER (SYNC) - RECEIVED  (same HTTP thread — blocks here)\n  3. EVENT LISTENER (SYNC) - DONE      (same HTTP thread)\n  4. CONTROLLER - RETURNING            (HTTP thread — HTTP 200 sent)\n  5. EVENT LISTENER (ASYNC) - RECEIVED (task-N thread — fires AFTER response)\n  6. EVENT LISTENER (ASYNC) - DONE     (task-N thread — ~500ms later)\n\nQuery params (both optional):\n  name  — included in the event payload (default: Demo User)\n  email — included in the event payload (default: demo@example.com)\n\nStack: Filter → Interceptor → AOP → Controller → publishEvent() → sync listener (HTTP thread) + async listener (task-N) → HTTP 200"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has expected fields\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.message).to.include('UserProcessedEvent published');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.name).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.email).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.hint).to.exist;",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Flow 9 — Security Layer (SecurityFilterChain / @PreAuthorize / @PostAuthorize)",
      "description": "FLOW 9 — Security Layer demo. Tests URL-level rules (SecurityFilterChain) and method-level rules (@PreAuthorize / @PostAuthorize).\n\nDemo users:\n  user  / pass123  → ROLE_USER\n  admin / admin123 → ROLE_USER + ROLE_ADMIN\n\nRecommended sequence:\n  9a — public   : no auth           → 200\n  9b — user-only: user:pass123      → 200  (authenticated)\n  9b — user-only: no auth           → 401  (unauthenticated)\n  9c — admin-only: admin:admin123   → 200  (ROLE_ADMIN)\n  9c — admin-only: user:pass123     → 403  (ROLE_USER, URL-level block)\n  9d — method-owned owner=user: user:pass123  → 200  (@PostAuthorize owner==caller)\n  9d — method-owned owner=admin: user:pass123 → 403  (@PostAuthorize blocks different owner)\n  9d — method-owned owner=user: admin:admin123→ 200  (@PostAuthorize hasRole(ADMIN) passes)\n\nAuth: HTTP Basic — set Authorization header to Basic base64(username:password).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Flow 9a — Public (no auth required)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/secure/public",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "secure", "public"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 9a — SecurityFilterChain permitAll.\n\nNo credentials required. SecurityFilterChain URL rule: .requestMatchers('/secure/public').permitAll().\n\nStack: SecurityFilterChain (permitAll) → LoggingFilter → Interceptor → AOP → Controller → SecuredDemoService.getPublicData() → 200"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200 — no auth needed\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Public data returned\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.security).to.eql('none');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data).to.include('Public');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 9b — User-Only (ROLE_USER or ROLE_ADMIN) — user credentials",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Basic dXNlcjpwYXNzMTIz",
                "description": "user:pass123 encoded in Base64",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/secure/user-only",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "secure", "user-only"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 9b — SecurityFilterChain authenticated() + @PreAuthorize(isAuthenticated).\n\nCredentials: user / pass123 (ROLE_USER).\nAuthorization: Basic dXNlcjpwYXNzMTIz   (base64 of 'user:pass123')\n\nStack: SecurityFilterChain (authenticated ✓) → Interceptor → AOP → Controller → @PreAuthorize(isAuthenticated ✓) → SecuredDemoService → 200"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200 — user credentials accepted\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"@PreAuthorize confirmed\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.caller).to.eql('user');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.annotation).to.eql('@PreAuthorize');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 9b — User-Only — NO credentials → 401",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/secure/user-only",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "secure", "user-only"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 9b exception branch — no Authorization header.\n\nSecurityFilterChain rejects BEFORE the request reaches the controller.\n401 Unauthorized is returned by Spring Security's BasicAuthenticationEntryPoint."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 401 — no credentials\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 9c — Admin-Only — admin credentials → 200",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Basic YWRtaW46YWRtaW4xMjM=",
                "description": "admin:admin123 encoded in Base64",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/secure/admin-only",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "secure", "admin-only"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 9c — SecurityFilterChain hasRole('ADMIN') + @PreAuthorize(hasRole('ADMIN')).\n\nCredentials: admin / admin123 (ROLE_USER + ROLE_ADMIN).\nAuthorization: Basic YWRtaW46YWRtaW4xMjM=  (base64 of 'admin:admin123')\n\nStack: SecurityFilterChain (hasRole ADMIN ✓) → @PreAuthorize(hasRole ADMIN ✓) → SecuredDemoService → 200"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200 — admin credentials accepted\", () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"@PreAuthorize ADMIN confirmed\", () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.caller).to.eql('admin');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.annotation).to.eql('@PreAuthorize');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Flow 9c — Admin-Only — user credentials → 403",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Basic dXNlcjpwYXNzMTIz",
                "description": "user:pass123 encoded in Base64",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/users/secure/admin-only",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "secure", "admin-only"]
            },
            "description": "FLOW 9c exception branch — wrong role.\n\nCredentials: user / pass123 (ROLE_USER only).\nAuthenticated ✓ but not ROLE_ADMIN → SecurityFilterChain returns 403 Forbidden before controller runs."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
